    .container.faq
        .sm_container
            .s_title Frequently asked question
            .sub_title Here you can find answers to questions that usually are interesting for people. Just honest and informed solar energy contractors who foster a passion for making clean energy more accessible.
        .faq_list
            -for(var f=1;f<=6;f++)
                .faq_list_item
                    .faq_list_item_head
                        span.icon
                        .text Can I really go solar for little to $0 down?
                    .faq_list_item_body
                        p Brightbox, our holistic home solar battery storage service, can help you power through outages and bill spikes, day and night. It could also help you save money compared to gas- or diesel-powered generators. No fumes, no noise, and no-hassle—Brightbox is fueled every time the sun is out.
                        p See the states where Sunrun is currently available and which solar incentives might be offered in your area. Some of the most common incentives include state tax credits, property and sales tax exemptions, Solar Renewable Energy Credits (SRECs), and rebates from your local utility. No matter what state you live in, you can also be eligible for the federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC) if you purchase your own solar system.

                        p Due to tech compatibility, Brightbox is only available with the installation of a new Sunrun home solar system. Check if Brightbox battery storage is offered in your area.




